rComments: Myers is my favorite professor at UTM. She is very clear on her expectations and lectures and explains her theories very well. Midterms: The lectures are very important, her questions are straight from her lecture notes. If you take a third year class the final essay is a lot harder! but overall great course!

By far one of the greatest sociology professors that have taught at the university. She's extremely helpful and turns very dull course content into intriguing lectures that inspires critical thinking. It's sad to see that this was the last lecture she will be teaching at UTM, but definitely deserves a good rating from me! =)

This class was really interesting and the prof was amazing! her tests are based on lectures mostly so be sure to go. and she talks really fast so it's best if you use a laptop to take down all the information

Really great prof! She is definitely approachable, tries her best to convey the material in the most easy to comprehend way possible, ensures class engagement with content by asking questions during lecture, and promptly answers questions within a reasonable time frame. I am currently taking SOC219 with her - looking forward to doing really well!
Myers made a very boring class rather intriguing. She is approachable, and willing to assist you if needed
Really approachable teacher, lectures are not the most interesting. But if you attend each class you should be good. Read the articles she provides. And compare whats repeated in lecture.
